# Cursor Rules

This project builds a low-cost AI desktop companion: a pixel-style "person trapped in a box" with memory, personality, chat, later voice, and eventual hardware support.

## Binding Doctrine

Read `AGENTS.md` first. Its authenticity doctrine, exact list of retired relationship guardrails,
2019 Intel Mac hardware envelope, and mandatory open-source/nearest-neighbor workflow are always
binding. `AGENTS.md` is not historical. Do not reintroduce those guardrails, polite-assistant
sanitization, or a custom subsystem when a stronger reusable implementation exists.

## Read Before Editing

Canonical entry — read only these to learn current state:

- `docs/HANDOFF.md`
- `docs/MVP_STATUS.md` — 进度记分牌 + 下一步 + 文档地图（§F）
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE_SNAPSHOT.md`
- `docs/TASK_QUEUE.md` — when expanding into a concrete task

> Historical (do NOT treat as current state; read only if a task points to them):
> `docs/PROJECT_BRIEF.md`, `docs/SESSION_PROTOCOL.md`, `docs/MVP_ROADMAP.md`,
> `docs/CURSOR_PHASE_PLAYBOOK.md`, `docs/TODO.md`, `docs/SESSION_LOG.md`, `docs/OPEN_SOURCE_REUSE.md`,
> and all `SD*/V2_*/VE*/VM*/PHASE_*/P9_*` specs. Full doc map: `docs/MVP_STATUS.md` §F.

## Cursor Role

Cursor is best used for:

- Pixel UI polish.
- CSS and animation timing.
- Small frontend components.
- Focused refactors after the architecture is already defined.
- Most feature implementation, if it follows `docs/CURSOR_PHASE_PLAYBOOK.md`.

Avoid changing these without explicit user approval and doc updates:

- Provider abstraction.
- SQLite memory schema.
- Behavior engine decision contract.
- File permission policy.
- Cost and token budget policy.

## Open Source

Before editing a module, search its current open-source nearest neighbors. If a maintained project is
materially ahead, integrate, adapt, or migrate to it; studying it and then rebuilding a smaller
version is not acceptable reuse. The present architecture is not a reason to reject a stronger
upstream. Record evidence and decisions in `docs/OPEN_SOURCE_REUSE.md`. Compute-heavy candidates
are deferred for hardware, never replaced by weaker custom code.

## UI Direction

- The character should feel like a small trapped person, not a normal chatbot avatar.
- Support idle, happy, sad, angry, sleepy, thinking, talking, worried, annoyed, and muted/silent states.
- Do not turn the UI into a marketing landing page.
- Prioritize the actual companion screen as the first view.

## Phase Execution

For each new Cursor chat, pick one phase or one phase slice from `docs/CURSOR_PHASE_PLAYBOOK.md`.

At the end of the chat:

- Run the relevant checks.
- Update `docs/TODO.md`.
- Append to `docs/SESSION_LOG.md`.
- Record reused/adapted open-source sources in `docs/OPEN_SOURCE_REUSE.md`.
- Do not silently start the next phase.
